Token architectures are basically structures made up of different stakeholder groups bound together by a set of mechanisms which determine and limit the behavior of these stakeholder groups. So basically, we've identified three main types of mechanisms that can be used in token architectures, and those are utility mechanisms, governance mechanisms, and distribution mechanisms. Utility mechanisms determine what functionalities the token has in relation to the underlying protocol. Governance mechanisms determine what role tokens play in governing the protocol, and distribution mechanisms determine how tokens are distributed to different stakeholders. For the purpose of this short episode, we are only going to dive deeper into utility mechanisms and leave the rest for later episodes. So when you're designing your utility mechanisms, the rule of thumb is that a good utility mechanism either adds functionality to the token or reduces the velocity of the token, and ideally both at the same time. So token velocity is the number of times a token changes hands within a certain time frame. And you really want to come up with mechanisms that prevent your token from changing hands too often, because if they do, the prices of these tokens usually suffer. And there's a couple of ways to achieve this. For example, if you choose to implement a staking mechanism, you will be reducing the circulating supply of your tokens in relation to the total supply of your tokens. So some of the tokens will be locked in smart contracts or generally somewhere where it's kind of less likely for people to sell them. So if we take filecoin as an example, filecoin is a decentralized network for sharing idle storage resources. But if you want to provide storage to the protocol, you are required to stake a certain amount of filecoin tokens into the protocol. And this mechanism has a wide range of positive consequences for its token architecture, such as that it creates buy pressure for the token. Because in order to be able to provide your storage resources to filecoin, you first need to go to the market and buy some filecoin tokens. It also reduces the velocity of the token because you need to stake the tokens before participating. And this prevents you from, in theory, from behaving in a malicious way.
